1
00:00:10,440 --> 00:00:11,692
-It is a Christmas show,

2
00:00:11,692 --> 00:00:14,635
and we're on the set
of "Home Alone"
with Ariana Grande.

3
00:00:14,683 --> 00:00:18,259
It is a delight.
It is violent as hell.

4
00:00:18,259 --> 00:00:19,695
-It's "Home Alone,"
the horror movie.

5
00:00:19,695 --> 00:00:24,228
-This is the fifth
of the sick, twisted series
that Mikey and Colin like to do.

6
00:00:24,228 --> 00:00:27,078
-Colin and I
have done a lot of violent ones.

7
00:00:27,078 --> 00:00:28,678
A lot of heads
getting chopped off.

8
00:00:28,678 --> 00:00:30,450
We obviously love "Home Alone."

9
00:00:30,450 --> 00:00:34,400
-We wanted to have a mix
of the real booby traps
from "Home Alone,"

10
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:37,951
and then we were
under the assumption
that Kevin McCallister
had set up other,

11
00:00:37,951 --> 00:00:41,120
perhaps even more violent traps
that we never got to see.

12
00:00:41,120 --> 00:00:42,395
And now we do.

13
00:00:42,395 --> 00:00:44,802
-You have Ariana
as Kevin McCallister.

14
00:00:44,802 --> 00:00:47,549
-Luckily, she was really into
being sprayed with blood.

15
00:00:47,549 --> 00:00:49,980
-Ariana was like, "I want
as much blood as possible.

16
00:00:50,050 --> 00:00:53,030
I want to look like Carrie
by the end of this thing."

17
00:00:57,090 --> 00:00:58,620
-I'm Kate McCallister.

18
00:00:58,690 --> 00:01:01,900
I just love Catherine O'Hara
so much,

19
00:01:01,900 --> 00:01:03,731
and she plays it so earnestly.

20
00:01:03,731 --> 00:01:07,034
You know, it's just...
this made me want to be
in a Christmas movie.

21
00:01:07,034 --> 00:01:07,970
This is my audition.

22
00:01:07,970 --> 00:01:08,973
-What's up, dorks?

23
00:01:08,973 --> 00:01:10,834
I'm playing the role of Buzz.

24
00:01:10,834 --> 00:01:15,211
Colin texted a picture of Buzz
and said, "Should I play buzz?"

25
00:01:15,211 --> 00:01:18,045
And it was immediately like,
"Yes."

26
00:01:18,045 --> 00:01:20,840
This actually looks like me
in eighth grade.

27
00:01:20,840 --> 00:01:24,873
-It's wild to work with him
or look at him
when he's dressed like that.

28
00:01:24,873 --> 00:01:26,202
It makes work impossible.

29
00:01:26,202 --> 00:01:27,145
-Hey, barf nuts.

30
00:01:27,145 --> 00:01:29,502
-I'm about to be bullied
by this dude.

31
00:01:29,502 --> 00:01:32,955
-"Home Alone" --
it's a classic, it's iconic.

32
00:01:32,955 --> 00:01:34,798
The pressure's on
to get it right.

33
00:01:34,798 --> 00:01:39,269
-So it's really important
that we match up everything
as close as humanly possible.

34
00:01:39,269 --> 00:01:41,981
We tried to match
the camera movements,
shot for shot,

35
00:01:41,981 --> 00:01:44,261
like when Kevin's
coming down the stairs
and, like, looking out,

36
00:01:44,261 --> 00:01:46,896
and then his mom
kind of peeks out
from behind the wall there,

37
00:01:46,896 --> 00:01:49,708
and it's like we're doing
that exact same shot
with the exact same set.

38
00:01:49,708 --> 00:01:52,134
We have this, like,
one-to-one replica of the house.

39
00:01:52,134 --> 00:01:55,111
-For the house, it's about
getting the wallpaper right.

40
00:01:55,111 --> 00:02:00,130
So the graphics department
had to, from scratch,
recreate all of the wallpaper.

41
00:02:00,130 --> 00:02:02,640
-All the wardrobe is, like,
custom made.

42
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:04,462
-There's always something
that gets you.

43
00:02:04,462 --> 00:02:08,192
For most of the scene,
Kevin wears a green robe.

44
00:02:08,192 --> 00:02:10,214
For some reason,
no one has that robe this year.

45
00:02:10,214 --> 00:02:15,159
So I went to a fabric store,
got the last
two and a half yards

46
00:02:15,159 --> 00:02:18,681
and was like, "Please, Sam,
please make a robe."

47
00:02:18,681 --> 00:02:21,139
-There's choreography,
there's stunts.

48
00:02:21,139 --> 00:02:22,333
-There's a lot of VFX,

49
00:02:22,333 --> 00:02:25,345
a lot of tricky, finicky
practical effects

50
00:02:25,345 --> 00:02:26,466
mixed with digital effects.

51
00:02:26,466 --> 00:02:29,406
We have the best team working
to throw this all together

52
00:02:29,406 --> 00:02:31,518
in a not-ideal amount of time.

53
00:02:31,518 --> 00:02:35,488
It takes a village
to make Bowen's arm fly off
and spray blood everywhere.

54
00:02:35,488 --> 00:02:38,854
At this point, we know
that this is
Bowen's last episode,

55
00:02:38,854 --> 00:02:42,653
and it is a beautiful thing
that his last shot on Film Unit

56
00:02:42,653 --> 00:02:45,327
is him getting
his arm ripped off
and spraying blood everywhere.

57
00:02:45,327 --> 00:02:46,578
It brought a tear to my eye.

58
00:02:46,578 --> 00:02:49,169
-That is a wrap on Bowen!

59
00:02:49,169 --> 00:02:53,402
-It's crazy that we're able
to pull all this stuff off.

60
00:02:53,402 --> 00:02:56,343
This is, like, my fifth season,
and it's still mind-blowing.

